column1: The hell is that...? A machine gun?

And it's topped with a security camera, too. It'll
probably open fire if you get too close.
So it's the same setup we saw in Shibuya...

The castle's beyond here. So we're gonna have
to do something about this thing first.

If I had to guess, I'd say there's a core
somewhere around here that's powering it.

I saw something that looked like a Prison Keep
up top. If this is business as usual, it's probably
there.
Then, I guess that's our first stop. Let's get goin'!

...Prison Keep? Well, I guess I'll know once I get
there.

Greetings, good citizens. Have you seen any
evildoers nearby?

If you do see any, please report it immediately.
Our hero will then come to change their hearts.

Akira is our one true hero. He is the only one
who can save the world.

Akira will keep everyone safe with the power to
change hearts. He will protect our way of life.

It must be referring to Konoe. I guess he's a
superhero in this world.

So this is how he views himself. Ironic that the
villain is playing the hero.

A phony hero parading himself around in a
futuristic city... Getting some major dystopia
vibes from this one.

So does that mean we're the villains? Heh, what
a load of crap.
We'll expose him for what he is.
Yes. Everyone will know the truth.

Who knows? This isn't your everyday narcissist
we're dealing with...

That's a good point! If we're going to oppose the
hero, then Super Phantom Thieves works great!

He wants to treat us like the bad guys? Fine.
We're still gonna bring him down!
We'll show him who the real villain is.

Keeping everyone safe with the power to
change hearts? What does it mean by that?
And this voice... Is that EMMA?
